    <stitle>STARTING MOTORS - PINION CLEARANCE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>PINION CLEARANCE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="2">
            <title>37-MT</title>
            <para>To check pinion or drive clearance follow the steps listed below:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove "M" terminal nut and insulate motor winding connector from "M" terminal stud.
                    Push connector about 1/8" away from back nut to clear nut and stud. Place insulating material (like
                    cloth) between connector and nut and stud.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect battery positive "S" terminal and negative to a clean metal ground on solenoid
                    case (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0803620">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0803620" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0803620" filename="../figg08/G0803620.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Connections for Checking Pinion Clearance, 37-MT</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">MOMENTARILY flash a jumper lead from ground to terminal "M". The drive will now shift
                    into cranking position and remain so until the battery is disconnected.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Push the pinion or drive back towards the commutator end to eliminate slack movement.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure the distance between pinion and retainer (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0803621">Figure 21</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0803621" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0803621" filename="../figg08/G0803621.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Checking Pinion Clearance, 37-MT</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. PRESS ON CLUTCH AS SHOWN TO TAKE UP MOVEMENT</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. PINION</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. RETAINER</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. .010" TO .070" PINION CLEARANCE</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. FEELER GAUGE</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Adjust clearance by removing plug and turning shaft nut (visible in
                    <hotlnk document="s08036_1.xml" xrefid="f0803601">Figure 1</hotlnk>and
                    <hotlnk document="s08036_1.xml" xrefid="f0803603">Figure 3</hotlnk>). Although typical
                    specifications are shown, always refer to specifications applying to specific models.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
